l plane client\n33: - [ ] Create `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/__init__.py`\n34: - [ ] Create `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n35: - [ ] Implement `ControlPlaneClient.__init__(workload_manager_url, auth_token=None)`:\n36:   - [ ] Resolve URL from arg or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env var\n37:   - [ ] Resolve token from arg or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`\n38:   - [ ] Create `requests.Session` with connection pooling\n39:   - [ ] Set `Authorization: Bearer {token}` header if token present\n40: - [ ] Implement `create_session(name, namespace, metadata=None, ttl=3600) -> str`:\n41:   - [ ] POST to `/v1/code-interpreter` with JSON `{name, namespace, ttl, metadata}`\n42:   - [ ] Return `data[\"sessionId\"]` or raise `ValueError`\n43: - [ ] Implement `delete_session(session_id) -> bool`:\n44:   - [ ] DELETE to `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}`\n45:   - [ ] Return `True` on 404 or success, `False` on other errors\n46: \n47: ### T005: Code Interpreter data plane client\n48: - [ ] Create `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n49: - [ ] Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.__init__(router_url, namespace, cr_name, session_id, timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)`:\n50:   - [ ] Build base URL using `urljoin`\n51:   - [ ] Create `requests.Session`\n52:   - [ ] Set default header `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n53: - [ ] Implement `_request(method, path, **kwargs)`:\n54:   - [ ] Add timeout tuple `(connect_timeout, read_timeout)`\n55:   - [ ] Raise on HTTP errors\n56: - [ ] Implement `execute_command(command, timeout=None) -> dict`:\n57:   - [ ] POST to `api/execute` with JSON `{command: [...], timeout: \"<n>s\"}`\n58:   - [ ] Raise `CommandExecutionError` if `exit_code != 0`\n59: - [ ] Implement `write_file(path, content, mode=\"0644\")`:\n60:   - [ ] POST to `api/files` with base64-encoded content\n61: - [ ] Implement `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)`:\n62:   - [ ] Multipart POST to `api/files`\n63: - [ ] Implement `download_file(remote_path, local_path)`:\n64:   - [ ] GET from `api/files/{path}`, stream response to file\n65: - [ ] Implement `list_files(path) -> list`:\n66:   - [ ] GET from `api/files?path={path}`\n67: \n68: ### T006: Agent Runtime data plane client\n69: - [ ] Create `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n70: - [ ] Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`:\n71:   - [ ] Class constant `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n72:   - [ ] `__init__(router_url, namespace, agent_name, session_id, timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)`:\n73:     - [ ] Build invocation base URL\n74:     - [ ] Create `requests.Session`\n75:   - [ ] `_request(method, path, **kwargs)`:\n76:     - [ ] Add timeout tuple\n77:   - [ ] `invoke(payload, timeout=None) -> dict`:\n78:     - [ ] POST JSON to invocation URL\n79:     - [ ] Set `SESSION_HEADER` and `Content-Type` headers\n80: \n81: ### T007: HTTP utility functions\n82: - [ ] Create `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/__init__.py`\n83: - [ ] Create `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n84: - [ ] Implement `read_token_from_file(path) -> str | None`:\n85:   - [ ] Read file, return stripped contents\n86:   - [ ] Handle `FileNotFoundError`, return `None`\n87: - [ ] Implement `create_session(timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0) -> tuple`:\n88:   - [ ] Create `requests.Session`\n89:   - [ ] Mount `HTTPAdapter` with pool settings\n90:   - [ ] Return `(session, timeout)` tuple\n91: \n92: ### T008: General utility functions\n93: - [ ] Create `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/utils.py`\n94: - [ ] Implement `ensure_dir(path)`: create directory if not exists\n95: - [ ] Implement `generate_timestamp() -> str`: ISO format timestamp\n96: - [ ] Implement `base64_encode(data) -> str`: standard base64 encoding\n97: - [ ] Implement `base64_decode(s) -> bytes`: standard base64 decoding\n98: \n99: ### T009: Logging configuration\n100: - [ ] Create `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/log.py`\n101: - [ ] Implement `setup_logging(level=logging.INFO)`:\n102:   - [ ] Configure root logger with format\n103:   - [ ] Return logger instance\n104: \n105: ### T010: High-level Code Interpreter client\n106: - [ ] Create `sdk-python/agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n107: - [ ] Implement `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__(router_url, workload_manager_url=None, name=None, namespace=\"default\", session_id=None, ttl=3600, timeout=120)`:\n108:   - [ ] Validate `router_url` is provided (arg or `ROUTER_URL` env)\n109:   - [ ] Store config\n110:   - [ ] If `session_id` not provided:\n111:     - [ ] Create `ControlPlaneClient`\n112:     - [ ] Call `create_session()`\n113:     - [ ] Handle failure: delete session, re-raise\n114:   - [ ] Call `_init_data_plane()`\n115: - [ ] Implement `_init_data_plane()`:\n116:   - [ ] Create `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with `session_id`\n117: - [ ] Implement context manager protocol:\n118:   - [ ] `__enter__()`: return `self`\n119:   - [ ] `__exit__(exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb)`: call `stop()`\n120: - [ ] Implement `stop()`:\n121:   - [ ] Close data plane session\n122:   - [ ] If created session: call `delete_session()`\n123:   - [ ] Close control plane session\n124: - [ ] Implement `execute_command(command, timeout=None) -> dict`: delegate to data plane\n125: - [ ] Implement `run_code(code, language=\"python\") -> dict`:\n126:   - [ ] Write timestamped `.py` file\n127:   - [ ] Execute `python3 <file>`\n128: - [ ] Implement `write_file(path, content)`: delegate to data plane\n129: - [ ] Implement `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)`: delegate to data plane\n130: - [ ] Implement `download_file(remote_path, local_path)`: delegate to data plane\n131: - [ ] Implement `list_files(path) -> list`: delegate to data plane\n132: \n133: ### T011: High-level Agent Runtime client\n134: - [ ] Create `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n135: - [ ] Implement `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__(router_url, namespace, agent_name, session_id=None, timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)`:\n136:   - [ ] Store config\n137:   - [ ] If `session_id` not provided:\n138:     - [ ] GET from invocation base URL\n139:     - [ ] Read `x-agentcube-session-id` from response header\n140:     - [ ] Raise `ValueError` if missing\n141:   - [ ] Create `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n142: - [ ] Implement context manager protocol:\n143:   - [ ] `__enter__()`: return `self`\n144:   - [ ] `__exit__(exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb)`: call `close()`\n145: - [ ] Implement `close()`: close underlying session\n146: - [ ] Implement `invoke(payload, timeout=None) -> dict`:\n147:   - [ ] If no `session_id`: raise `ValueError`\n148:   - [ ] Delegate to data plane\n149: \n150: ---\n151: \n152: ## Verification\n153: \n154: - [ ] All 11 files created and match specifications\n155: - [ ] `pyproject.toml` valid TOML, installable via `pip install -e sdk-python/`\n156: - [ ] All imports resolve: `from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient`\n157: - [ ] Exception hierarchy testable: all custom exceptions inherit from `AgentCubeError`\n158: - [ ] Context managers work: `with CodeInterpreterClient(...) as client:` and `with AgentRuntimeClient(...) as client:`\n159: - [ ] No circular imports between modules\n160: - [ ] All HTTP clients use connection pooling\n161: - [ ] Token resolution from file path works (with graceful fallback)\n162: - [ ] Environment variable fallbacks work for URLs and tokens\n\n(End of file - total 162 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-033: Python SDK — Clients and Exceptions\n\n**Module**: root  \n**Language**: Python  \n**Size**: M (11 files)  \n**Status**: ST-3 completed  \n\n---\n\n## Tasks\n\n### T001: Project scaffolding and package metadata\n- [ ] Create `sdk-python/pyproject.toml` with build-system, project metadata, and dependencies\n- [ ] Verify `name = \"agentcube-sdk\"`, `version = \"0.0.10\"`, `requires-python = \">=3.10\"`\n- [ ] Verify dependencies: `requests>=2.31.0`, dev deps: `pytest>=7.0.0`, `pytest-cov>=4.0.0`\n- [ ] Verify `build-backend = \